title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 08
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: LibriVox recording of Popular History of Ireland Book 08 by D’Arcy McGee, read by Sibella Denton. Thomas D’Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 8, subtitled “The Era of the Reformation”, addresses the late Tudor period, particularly the reigns of the children of Henry VIII, and ends with the end of the reign of Elizabeth I. (Summary by Sibella Denton) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B audiobook of Complete Series
